Topic: SASE
Objective:
- Describe SASE (Secure Access Service Edge).
- Understand the core security features of a SASE solution.
- Understand the benefits of using SASE.

####
> Secure Access Service Edge (SASE)
Definition: Secure Access Service Edge (SASE) combines Network-as-a-Service and Security-as-a-Service to simplify complex network infrastructure.
Delivery Model: Provided through the cloud as an as-a-service consumption model.
Purpose: Supports secure access for distributed and hybrid enterprise networks.
Key Features: Enables work-from-anywhere with:
-Firewall as a Service (FWaaS)
-Secure Web Gateway (SWG)
-Zero-Trust Network Access (ZTNA)
-Threat detection functions
Components: Built from Security Service Edge (SSE) + SD-WAN.

> Benefits of SASE
Universal Secure Access: Protects users, workloads, devices, and applications regardless of location.
Remote Worker Security: Critical advantage for enabling safe work-from-anywhere.
Flexible & Consistent Security: Uniform protection across environments.
Reduced IT Cost & Complexity: Simplifies infrastructure management.
Fast, Seamless User Experience: Ensures efficiency without sacrificing security.

> Core Security Features of SASE
1. Software-Defined Wide Area Network (SD-WAN)
Streamlines operations with overlay structure
Directs traffic efficiently for internet, cloud apps, and data centers
Enables fast app deployment and policy management across locations

2. Secure Web Gateway (SWG)
Protects users, devices, and apps from online threats
Filters malware, prevents data loss
Enforces internet policy compliance

3. Firewall-as-a-Service (FWaaS)
Cloud-based replacement for physical firewalls
Provides NGFW capabilities: IPS, Anti-Malware, SSL Inspection, Sandbox

4. Cloud Access Security Broker (CASB)
Secures cloud usage across public, private, and SaaS environments
Prevents data leaks, malware infection, and compliance issues

5.Zero Trust Network Access (ZTNA)
Grants secure access to internal apps for remote users
No automatic trust; every access attempt is verified
Uses MFA, NAC, and policy enforcement

6.Centralized Management
Single console for all security features
Streamlines change control, patching, outage coordination, and policy administration
Ensures consistent policies across the organization


